  "prompt": "When one should eat after workout?",
  "response": "The timing of post-workout nutrition is important for optimal recovery and muscle growth. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. Immediate post-workout (within 30 minutes):\n- Consume a combination of protein and carbohydrates\n- Helps replenish glycogen stores and start muscle recovery\n- Especially important after intense or long workouts\n\n2. Ideal timing:\n- 30-45 minutes after exercise is considered the \"anabolic window\"\n- Best time to consume protein and carbs for muscle repair and growth\n\n3. Specific recommendations:\n- Protein: 20-30 grams\n- Carbohydrates: 0.5-0.7 grams per pound of body weight\n- Can be in the form of:\n  * Protein shake\n  * Lean meat\n  * Greek yogurt\n  * Protein bar\n  * Smoothie with protein powder\n\n4. Factors affecting timing:\n- Type of workout\n- Intensity of exercise\n- Personal fitness goals\n- Individual metabolism\n\n5. If unable to eat immediately:\n- Try to eat within 1-2 hours after workout\n- Still beneficial for recovery\n\nNote: Individual needs may vary, so consulting a nutritionist or fitness professional can provide personalized advice.",
